Title: Necessity is the Mother of Invention Ep.1
SubTitle: No Translation

Text:
A laboratory doubling as a private bedroomâ€”among the
equipment and materials strewn all over the place, the
gentle sounds of its slumbering mistress can be heard.

For her, each item may be in the perfect place, but to
anyone else it is nearly impossible to navigate.
Geez... If only she would clean up a little.

Following her encounter with a hefty book that had
fallen on the floor, Gamma proceeds more carefully
towards the figure sleeping on the bed.

Amazingly, she makes it to the bed without even
falling over once.
Come on, Eta! No going back to bed!

As Gamma shakes Eta by her shoulders, her arm
bumps into the pile of research materials piled up
nearby, causing them to topple over.

Eta sits up, rubbing her eyes, her wobbling torso
betraying her inclination to topple back onto the
bed.
On the cart at the door to this lab.

That's not an option, not when I can barely even
find space to walk.

That's not an option either. Come on. Annoying
though it may be, you need to eat.

Don't neglect your meals just because Epsilon is out
on a mission.

Eta's head continues to wobble, even as Gamma
lectures her.

Make sure you eat. I'll come check up on you again
later.
I can't even tell whether she's heard me or not...

Gamma wants to make sure that Eta finishes eating,
but she, too, has her own mission to carry out.
Reluctantly, she turns around...

Making her way back out she falls over several times,
as she usually does.

Left alone, Eta wobbles back and forth a few more
times before flopping back onto the bed again.
Lady Alpha...asked me to do...some research for her.

Eta's eyes roam over the room. The pile of papers
that she wanted to look through are sitting halfway
across the room on a table.

Rolling over and pushing her sleepiness away,
she reaches out her hand...

The most efficient thing to do would be to get out
of bed and pick them up...but even that is too
much work.

Instead, Eta squirms her way over to the edge of the
bed.

Taking in a deep breath, she stretches out her hand
once again...

Her effort, if you could call it that, sees Eta's
fingers catch the edge of the tableâ€”
â€”before she falls out of the bed onto the groundâ€”

â€”pulling the entire table over, it's contents crashing
to the floor. Meanwhile, the papers in Eta's hand fly
into the air, settling haphazardly on top of her.

Despite all that, Eta shows no signs of getting
up off the ground.

While it does hurt, she is used to acquiring bumps
and bruises in her habitually semi-conscious state.
And so, she makes no fuss this time either.

Picking them all up...putting them back in order...
What a pain...
I'll just leave it...for next time.

Squirming slowly like a caterpillar, Eta crawls back
up onto the bed.

Flopping onto the bed she gazes up at the ceiling,
exhaling deeply as if she'd had a hard workout.

Shaken awake by her fall from the bed, Eta now
notices the delicious smells wafting from the
door, which has been left open.

The research materials...all scattered around...
And the food...just out of reach...

Ack... I guess...I'll have to...alter my body...so
that my arm can extend...
Have it come to me... Inconvenience is...bad...

Eta leaps up, the intensity belying her
characteristically sluggish movements.

She searches the vicinity, her gaze stopping at the
food-laden cart just outside the laboratory door.

To the caster...using magic circuits... Having it come
here...automatically... What I need...for that...

If Eta's master, Cid, had seen her at this point, he
surely would have commented on how a switch
within her must have been flipped.

Only minutes ago, getting out of bed was a monumental
effort, but that version of her vanishes like a mirage.

...replaced by a girl who leaps from her bed and
practically sprints over to her research desk.
